4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would propose an amendment to the
6 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, relating to public
7 K-12 schools, to require local boards of education to
8 adopt policies requiring each public K-12 school to
9 broadcast or sanction the performance of the first
10 stanza of The Star-Spangled Banner at least once per
11 week during school hours.
12
13
14 A BILL
15 TO BE ENTITLED
16 AN ACT
17
18 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
19 of 2022, to require local boards of education to adopt
20 policies requiring each public K-12 school to broadcast or
21 sanction the performance of the first stanza of The
22 Star-Spangled Banner at least once per week during school
23 hours.
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
25 Section 1. The Legislature finds and declares the
26 following:
27 (1) During the Battle of Baltimore of the War of 1812,
28 Francis Scott Key visited the British fleet in the Chesapeake
Page 1

Francis Scott Key visited the British fleet in the Chesapeake
HB572 INTRODUCED
29 Bay on September 7, 1814, to secure the release of Dr. William
30 Beanes, who had been captured after the British burned
31 Washington, D.C.
32 (2) The release of Dr. Beanes was secured, but Key and
33 Beanes were held by the British during the shelling of Fort
34 McHenry, one of the forts defending Baltimore.
35 (3) On the morning of September 14, 1814, after the
36 25-hour British bombardment of Fort McHenry, Key peered
37 through the clearing smoke to see a 42-foot by 30-foot
38 American flag flying proudly atop the fort.
39 (4) He was so inspired to see the enormous flag still
40 flying over the fort that he began penning a song, which he
41 named The Defence of Fort McHenry, to commemorate the
42 occasion, and he included a note that it should be sung to the
43 tune of the popular British melody To Anacreon in Heaven.
44 (5) In 1916, President Woodrow Wilson ordered that the
45 anthem, which had been popularly renamed The Star-Spangled
46 Banner, be played at military and naval occasions.
47 (6) On March 3, 1931, President Herbert Hoover signed a
48 resolution of Congress that officially designated The
49 Star-Spangled Banner as the National Anthem of the United
50 States.
51 (7) For over 100 years, The Star-Spangled Banner has
52 served to inspire generations of patriotic Americans, and it
53 is imperative that students have exposure to this history and
54 inspiration.
55 Section 2. The following amendment to the Constitution
56 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
Page 2

of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
HB572 INTRODUCED
57 (a) Each local board of education shall adopt a policy
58 requiring each public K-12 school under its jurisdiction to
59 broadcast The Star-Spangled Banner during school hours, at
60 least once per week.
61 (b)(1) A local board of education shall select for
62 broadcast, pursuant to subsection (a), any recording of the
63 first stanza of The Star-Spangled Banner that is archived
64 within the Library of Congress and available on the Library of
65 Congress website.
66 (2) A local board of education, alternatively, may
67 adopt a policy allowing, during school hours, for the
68 performance of the first stanza of The Star-Spangled Banner
69 from original sheet music, archived within the Library of
70 Congress and available on its website, by a school-sanctioned
71 band program, choral program, vocal group, or vocalist.
72 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
73 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
74 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
75 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
76 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
77 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
78 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
79 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
80 language; and translate effective dates.
81 Section 3. An election upon the proposed amendment
82 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284 and 285 of the
83 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws of this
84 state. The appropriate election official shall assign a ballot
